Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Hoff provides a massive, massive scalp for the hosts. The Aussies are all pumped up as they see the back of Virat. India are 3 down now and in heaps of trouble in this West Test.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mitchell Starc gets his second wicket and India are four down now. An appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. The Aussies have already started celebrating but no reaction from the umpire there. A review has been taken straight away. Starc hits the hard length, on off and gets it to deviate a bit away from the right-hander. KL Rahul takes a half stride forward and tries to meet the ball under the nose. He though plays inside the line as the ball nips away. It passes close to the bat and Alex Carey, the keeper does the rest. UltraEdge comes up and shows a sharp spike when the ball passes the bat. KL's bat also comes in contact with his front pad right after but the umpire deems that it contacted the ball first. Hence, it is given OUT! KL Rahul is not happy with the decision as he thinks that it hit his flap of the pad first. KL who looked well-settled departs now, on 26 (74) with less than ten minutes to Lunch.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Jasprit Bumrah leading from the front and it's game on here in Perth! Commentary: OUT! LBW! Jasprit Bumrah is on a roll and what a call by the on-air commentator as well. Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Siraj gets in on the act now! Good low take by Rahul!  Siraj pulls the length back as he bends his back and hits the deck hard, on a shortish length, on off. Marsh gets on his toes to ride the bounce and defend it out with a straight bat. The outside edge is found and it goes low towards the slip cordon as Marsh tries to take one hand off the bat. It goes low to the left of third slip where Rahul stays low and dives to his left to take the catch. India start to celebrate but Marsh is asked to wait as the third umpire is called into action to check for a fair catch. The third umpire looks at a couple of angles and then deems that Rahul had his fingers clearly underneath the ball. Australia have now lost half their side with just 38 on the board and trailing by 112 runs.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR...RISHABH PANT TAKES IT THIS TIME! Harshit Rana finally ends this frustrating 10th-wicket partnership and claims his third wicket. Rana steams in from around the stumps and hones in a fractionally fuller-length delivery, attacking the stumps. Mitchell Starc gets his front foot out of the way and creates room for himself. Goes for a big heave across but only manages to get a top edge. Skies it behind the wickets and swirls over the slip cordon. Virat Kohli prepares himself for the catch but it is Rishabh Pant who calls for his catch, locks his eyes on the ball, settles under it and takes it safely. India have bowled Australia out for 104 to gain a handy lead of 46 runs!

Commentary: BUZZERS!!! A mix-up of all sorts! Indecision by the batters between the wickets, followed by a wayward throw at the bowler's end. A direct hit and KL Rahul was well gone for miles. Commentary: HUNDRED FOR JAISWAL! He has redeemed himself after a duck in the first innings by scoring an impressive hundred on his maiden tour of Australia. Jaiswal becomes only the third Indian batter after ML Jaisimha and Sunil Gavaskar to notch up a ton in his first Test in Australia. Also, as per the broadcasters, Jaiswal achieves this feat as the fourth youngest Test centurion on Australian soil after Sachin Tendulkar, Rishabh Pant, and Dattu Phadkar. Coming to the delivery, Hazlewood bangs it into the deck, on off and middle, Yashasvi Jaiswal arches back and tries to ramp it over the keeper. Does not get it exactly where he intended and gets more height than distance on it. It goes well fine of deep fine leg. The third umpire is called into action for a boundary check and the replay shows that the ball hit the boundary cushions on the full. As soon as the six is signaled, Jaiswal takes the helmet off and has his arms aloft in celebration. Gets a huge round of applause from the crowd at the Optus and also from the Indian dugout.

Commentary: Jaiswal was gone for all money had the throw hit A couple of nervy moments for Jaiswal since bringing up his ton. Starc serves it on a length, on off, Rahul firms the drive and it goes along the ground towards mid off. Jaiswal sets off for the run but it was hit sweetly and it did not take long for the ball to travel to mid off. Pat Cummins picks it up cleanly and has a shy at the bowling end. Jaiswal turns around after being sent back and he is nowhere in the frame as he has given up. Cummins fails to hit the stumps at the bowling end by a whisker.

Commentary: BUZZERS! Mitchell Starc bowls it fuller in length and keeps the line around the off-stump. Rahul drives it wide of the cover fielder, where Cummins scoots from mid off to his left and half-stops on the dive, and allows a single. He collects the ball and overthrows, having a shy at the batting end, and with no proper backup, the ball rolls towards the deep backward point region, allowing the batters to get another run.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Mitchell Starc breaks through! Finally, an edge goes to hand for Australia. Starc angles it in from around the wicket, on a length, around off, Rahul is forced to play at it due to the angle as he presents a straight bat to defend. The ball straightens enough to catch the feather of an outside edge and it goes low towards the keeper. Alex Carey stays low and gets his gloves cleanly underneath the ball to complete a safe catch. Muted celebrations from the hosts and understandably so. The 201-run opening partnership off 383 balls is broken now. Rahul goes for 77 (176). India are 201/1, leading by 247 runs.
Default_Commentary: 62.6: Mitchell Starc to KL Rahul, OUT! c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Josh Hazlewood strikes on the very first delivery after Lunch. However, the decision has been sent upstairs by the two on-field umpires for a fair catch check. Coming to the delivery, Josh Hazlewood charges in from around the stumps and lands it on a good length, angling on the off-stump, Devdutt Padikkal prods forward on the front foot to block it out. But the ball nips a shade away from the left-hander and hence, a healthy outside edge is found. The ball goes flat and low towards the second slip where Steven Smith stays low and takes a sharp catch to his left, just above the grass. Padikkal falls for 25 (71). India are 275/2, leading by 321 runs.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! What a sharp catch by Dhruv Jurel at short leg! Washington Sundar stays around the stumps and slows down the pace, giving some flight on it. Keeps the line of attack on the stumps and the length is full. Mitchell Starc prods forward and brings his bat ahead of the pads to clip it away. But he is a bit early into the shot and ends up lobbing it towards the right of short leg where Jurel shows quick reflexes. He stays in his squatting position but stretches his right hand out, almost thrusting it over his head, and plucks it out of thin air. Starc departs on 12 (35). Sundar gets his first wicket and Australia are 227/8 now. And that will be TEA ON DAY 4!

Commentary: OUT! BOWLED'EM! INDIA WIN A FAMOUS TEST IN PERTH! A victory which will be remembered for a long, long time! Harshit Rana stays around the stumps and serves the slower ball at 109.9 kph that lands on a fuller length at off, Alex Carey is stuck inside the crease and goes through to push it to the off-side, anticipating the ball to come quicker at him. He ends up playing inside the line and goes through the shot a bit early. The ball flirts past the outside edge to clatter into the sticks. India halt Australia's unbeaten winning streak at the Optus Stadium in Perth. Also, this is the largest win for the tourists in terms of the run margin in Australia.
